   
    1.😀 Scheduling Queues In Process Management || Queue Diagram Representation of process scheduling?
      Scheduling queues are used by the OS to manage processes waiting for execution.
    ✅ Types:
      Job Queue → all processes in the system
      Ready Queue → processes waiting for CPU
      Device Queue → processes waiting for I/O
    🔄 Flow:
       Job Queue → Ready Queue
       Ready Queue → CPU (Running)
       Running → Device Queue (for I/O)
       After I/O → back to Ready Queue 


   2.😒Types of Schedulers In Operating Sysyem || Long Term Scheduler || Short Term || Medium Term || OS
      🧠 Types of Schedulers in Operating System
         Schedulers decide which process runs and when.

       ✅ 1. Long-Term Scheduler (Job Scheduler)
           Selects processes from Job Queue → Ready Queue
           Controls number of processes in memory
           👉 Runs less frequently

       ✅ 2. Short-Term Scheduler (CPU Scheduler)
           Selects process from Ready Queue → CPU
           Decides which process executes next
           👉 Runs very frequently (fast)

       ✅ 3. Medium-Term Scheduler
            Temporarily removes (suspend) / adds processes from memory
            Helps in swapping to control memory usage     